## Complete Startup Guide

---

**Step 1 — Open Terminal 1 and start Flask:**
```powershell
cd "D:\Full stack Development\ai-interior-designer-v2\backend"
venv\Scripts\activate
python app.py
```
Wait for `Running on http://127.0.0.1:5000` — keep this terminal open.

---

**Step 2 — Open Terminal 2 and start React:**
```powershell
cd "D:\Full stack Development\ai-interior-designer-v2\frontend"
npm start
```
Wait for browser to open at `http://localhost:3000` — keep this terminal open.

---

**Step 3 — Open Google Colab and run cells in order:**

1. Imports
2. Cache directory
3. Load ControlNet
4. Load Stable Diffusion
5. Load Inpainting pipeline
6. Load YOLOv8
7. Load SAM
8. Helper functions
9. Style prompts
10. generate_style function
11. detect_objects function
12. edit_object function
13. Flask API + ngrok cell
14. ngrok auth token cell

Wait for the URL to print.

---

**Step 4 — Open Terminal 3 and register the Colab URL:**
```powershell
Invoke-WebRequest -Uri "http://localhost:5000/set-colab-url" -Method POST -ContentType "application/json" -Body '{"url": "https://elza-gradualistic-cyril.ngrok-free.dev"}'
```

---

**Step 5 — Verify everything is connected:**
```powershell
Invoke-WebRequest -Uri "http://localhost:5000/health" -Method GET
```
You should see `colab_connected: true`

---

**Step 6 — Open the app:**

Go to `http://localhost:3000` and you are ready.

---

**Important reminders:**
- Keep Terminal 1 (Flask) and Terminal 2 (React) open at all times
- The ngrok URL changes every session — always re-register it in Step 4
- If generation fails, check that Colab Flask cell is still running — re-run it if needed
- Models load from Google Drive so steps 3-7 in Colab are fast after first setup